common_examples.text: the traffic from thrissur to kochi was fine and weather is good

Last week, drove to/fro to attend a funeral at Ettumanoor. Route taken was Bangalore-Salem-Pollachi-Nenmara-Vadakancherry-MC Road-Ettumanoor. Took almost 11 hours including breaks. Kuthiran stretch roads were non existent.   While returning (25th- onam day), avoided Pollachi, and instead opted for the direct route. Time taken was 10 hours. Crossed Kuthiran stretch around 1630 hours, and traffic was much less compared to previous day. Sad to see the destruction and damage caused by flood/rain.

travel from thrissur to palakkad Kuthiran had low traffic at around 12:30 PM. Roads go from bad to worse to worst as you progress from start of tunnel section towards Pattikkad. Section between Kuthiran and Pattikkad is in its worst condition I've seen in a while.
Took the NH47 > Alathur > Pazhayannur > Chelakara > Wadakancherry > Thrissur. After you turn off from the highway, the roads are good albeit winding and narrow.
from Kodangallur toThrissur route is when the surface of road gets bad.
Drove from Palakkad to Kozhikode today. Took Mundur Kongad Cherpulassery Perinthalmanna route. The roads are very bad and almost non existant from Kongad to Mangalamkunnu.

entities.value: very bad and almost non existant

common_examples.text: I had travelled from Trivandrum to Ranny (Mannamaruthy) yesterday. The MC road upto Adoor is in good shape. I faced traffic jams in Venjaramood and Kottarakara, the delay of about 15 minutes waiting for the police to clear the traffic.I had travelled from Trivandrum to Ranny (Mannamaruthy) yesterday. The MC road upto Adoor is in good shape. I faced traffic jams in Venjaramood and Kottarakara, the delay of about 15 minutes waiting for the police to clear the traffic.Roads in Ranny and upto Mannamaruthy are in general ok with some potholed sections.

I did the Palakkad - Ottapalam - Kulappully - Thrissur stretch earlier this week and in spite of the monsoon rain it was a superb drive. Excellent road and the celebrated green of Valluvanad in all its glory. I was told the NH between Thrissur and Palakkad remains in a rotten state.

the road via Muvattupuzha, Thodupuzha, Kanhar, right? Those are the best roads in the state as of now. That crazy climb up Moolamattom to Naadukaani is just amazing. Then, carry on forward till Cheruthoni, Idukki and Ramakkalmedu to attain complete Nirwana. Something to be experienced atleast once in a lifetime.

There are unlimited attractions all the way from Cochin. The best being the Wild elephants and other animals near/before Painavu. The best is to take a powerful rear wheel drive one. Makes up for a perfect Weekend drive from here.

entities.value: Wild elephants and other animals near/before Painavu.

common_examples.text: Perinthalmanna till Pulamanthole is silky smooth and wider now with a relaid road. Pulamanthole >Pattambi > Perumbilavu is patched and some portions are relaid(manual) so good enuf to cruise at 50-60 kmph. The bridge at Palakkad-Thrissur district border (near Chalissery) is reconstructed and so a 75m wayside diversion is present which is very uneven and vehicles with low GC better watchout. Perumbilavu till Guruvayoor thru Kunnamkulam is as before with no issues

from cochin to Bangalore Traffic towards Blore was low but had huge number of trucks. Passed TCR toll at around 4.30am and the queue towards Cochin was long even during the wee hours.  Kuthiran is all good except for the slow traffic.Coimbatore bypass is a joke. Easily lost good time here. Like excepted, traffic towards Kerala was huge. Scanning the code each time takes a lot of time.

travel from thrissur to palakkad the ottapalam shornur route was good.its quickly reaches the destination.there were a kerala kalamandalam and nila river etc are the attractions.the weather is good.traffic is less

Travel from thrissur to palakkad,the route from wadakkanchery to chelakkara mayannur the road was very smooth.there have less traffic.there have good weather.that was a village area.so many trees and attractions are there.also pineapple vegetations we can see there
travel from thrissur to palakkad,the kuthiran road was huge traffic.

coimbatore-vaalayar-palakkad-trichur-angamaly-cochin is the route.....road work is going on upto vaalayar...from vaalayar to cochin 4 way road work is finished....now the road condition is good.....no need of pollachi route
Coimbatore to Valayar and Palakad to Thrissur sections are not good. But still, it is much better than any other route. Approx travel time-4.30 to 5.30 hrs depending on traffic.

entities.value: much better than any other route

common_examples.text: Coimbatore to Palakkad is direct and you have a good road. If you are travelling from Udumalpet and if you do not want to touch Coimbatore then rake a diversion in Pollachi to Palakkad. Road condition is ok but you save time and distance.

from thrissur to ernamkulam,the NH road services are excellent.its a good road.the weather conditions does not effect the roads.the traffic in school time and office times are huge.the night drive is ok
From Vadakkanchery to Thrissur is newly laid road now though it's single road (two lane) but traffic is heavy. I just came back to Palakkad on this stretch an hour back.
Roads from cochin to Munnar and from there to alapuzha are all fine good ..NH85 highway is narrow and traffic blocks are regular in the evening
Muvattupuzha-munnar route which is less congested in the early morning. the road has several dangerous curves that you had better be careful while cornering the curves.
Munnar is refreshingly cooler than the coast and other town. if you are visiting in January it is relatively warm other places in munnar the temperatures drop considerably after the sun goes down
From vaalayar to cochin 4 way road work is finished.. now the road condition is good
Kochi to kodaikkanal traffic was very less and enjoyed the drive only problem was between pollachi and palani
